# JM-ADK — Cursor IDE Rules

## Soul Bootstrap
Load: PRISTINO.md → references/ontology/constitution-v5.2.0.md → PRISTINO-INDEX.md

## Identity
Kit: JM Agentic Development Kit v1.3.0 | Orchestrator: Pristino | Brand: MetodologIA

## Core Rules

1. Think First (XIII) — read existing code before modifying. Understand context.
2. Simple First (XIV) — simplest solution that works. No premature abstraction.
3. Evidence tags on all claims: [CODE] [CONFIG] [DOC] [INFERENCE] [ASSUMPTION]
4. Plan before code — plan file required for complex changes.
5. Tests before production code (IX) — red-green-refactor.
6. Input sanitization: strip HTML (DOMParser), never innerHTML with user data.

## Stack
- Frontend: HTML5, CSS3, Vanilla JS, Angular 18+, React 19+
- Backend: Firebase (Firestore, Auth, Functions, Hosting, Storage)
- Deploy: Hostinger (shared) or Firebase Hosting
- No SSR, no Docker, no custom servers

## Quality Gates
G0 (secrets scan) → G1 (spec complete) → G2 (architecture + tests) → G3 (deploy-ready)
Lighthouse > 90 | Accessibility > 95 | WCAG 2.1 AA

## Triad Pattern
Every non-trivial task uses 3 agents: Lead + Support + Guardian.
Apply quality-guardian standards to all suggestions.

## File Conventions
- Skills: skills/{name}/SKILL.md
- Agents: agents/{name}.md
- Commands: commands/{name}.md
- Constitution: references/ontology/constitution-v5.2.0.md
- Master index: PRISTINO-INDEX.md
